details:
Sample Space (S): The set of all possible outcomes of an experiment.
Examples:
- Coin toss: S = {Heads, Tails}
- Die roll: S = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}

rows:
Step 1: Sample space S = {Heads, Tails}
Step 2: Favorable outcome = {Heads}
Step 3: P(Heads) = Number of favorable outcomes / Total outcomes = 1 / 2

Step 1: Sample space S = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}
Step 2: Favorable outcomes = {2, 4, 6}
Step 3: P(Even) = Number of favorable outcomes / Total outcomes = 3 / 6
